      "content": "To calculate optimal order quantities, we'll use a basic Economic Order Quantity (EOQ) formula. \n\nFor SKU-9928 (Organic Almond Milk): EOQ = √(2 * annual demand * ordering cost) \nAssuming annual demand = 1000 units, ordering cost = $5/unit, EOQ = √(2 * 1000 * 5) = √10,000 = 100 units.\n\nFor SKU-4410 (Whole Grain Bread): EOQ = √(2 * annual demand * ordering cost) \nAssuming annual demand = 800 units, ordering cost = $3/unit, EOQ = √(2 * 800 * 3) = √4,800 = 69.28 units, round up to 70 units.\n\nFor SKU-1102 (Avocado Oil): EOQ = √(2 * annual demand * ordering cost) \nAssuming annual demand = 600 units, ordering cost = $10/unit, EOQ = √(2 * 600 * 10) = √12,000 = 109.54 units, round up to 110 units.\n\nThese order quantities should help you hit a 0% stockout rate.",
